raw_response:
He begs most respectfully
to subscribe himself,
I’d chaunt his praises with a Poets fire;
Wake then my MUSE the gen’rous trump of fame,
And tho’ my garland may fall off, his plumes
Who while he tarries, feels no wish unbless’d;
Who makes his heavy burden weigh more light;
O if the man who makes a single blade,
Lift its green head above the parched glade;
Where never verdure did before appear,
And his immortal wreath untarnish’d shine.
By noble dealings and by actions kind;
Who tho’ he spurns the mean desire of pelf,
To make your Acres your high hopes repay;
See this plain truth, clear as the solar ray,
And see it proved in ev’ry joyous swain;
Diffuse abundance thro’ a steril land;
The Bailiff sinks, a cheerful Farmer sings;
Until dispers’d among the sons of earth;
Wisdom in Virtue ends, and thus he tries
Endeavouring so his image fair to show,
Could such a man then in the _shades_ remain,
Soon HOLKHAM’S glitt’ring turrets she discerned,
He flew to save her tho’ by foes oppress’d;
Allured by place ambitiously they rise,
Though the first patrons on whose wings they rose;
He had not sought these tempting lures in vain;
Though not with half the brilliance of his own;
He nail’d his colours to his country’s mast.
To rouse the COUNTRY and her ire excite;
On false pretences from the Country torn;
To make the Patriot his friends disown;
No venal act of his appears to wound,
Nor from the Peasant’s industry withdrawn
Or made the Oligarchal Tyrants strong;
His bright perfections with thy pencil faint;
Did not his instant patronage command;
The PRESS’ LIBERTY, the JURY’S right,
Sweet PEACE, to keep or to restore her reign,
With anxious heart our errors to explore;
This hope at length the grateful Patriot saw,
And what for fifty years he sought in vain,
And a NEW CHARTER, destined to endure,
He quits his public toils, resolved no more,
With grateful raptures may his heart still glow,
And ’MID THE PEERAGE o’er her weal preside;
The dazzling coronet which decks a Peer;
There see his Heirs adorn the name of COKE,
{16}  The Suspension of the HABEAS CORPUS ACT.
